xylanFltActiveAdminState.name: xylanFltActiveAdminState
xylanFltActiveAdminState.description: The current administrative state of the HRE-X filtering software.

xylanFltActiveOperState.name: xylanFltActiveOperState
xylanFltActiveOperState.description: The current operational state of the HRE-X filtering software. This is independent of the administrative state.

xylanFltConfigAdminState.name: xylanFltConfigAdminState
xylanFltConfigAdminState.description: The current configured administrative state of the HRE-X filtering software.

xylanFltGroupTable.name: xylanFltGroupTable
xylanFltGroupTable.description: Group entry for HRE-X filtering feature. This object contains a collection of Group objects when contain a list of filtering rules.

xylanFltGroupEntry.name: xylanFltGroupEntry
xylanFltGroupEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one Group.

xylanFltGroupIndex.name: xylanFltGroupIndex
xylanFltGroupIndex.description: The group index which is the octet string of printable characters containing the name of the group.

xylanFltGroupAdminState.name: xylanFltGroupAdminState
xylanFltGroupAdminState.description: The current status of this group. active (1) means the route is functioning, delete (2) tells SNMP to delete the route

xylanFltGroupProtocol.name: xylanFltGroupProtocol
xylanFltGroupProtocol.description: The protocol type of the group. This has significance with the index of the OIDs of the rules in the group.

xylanFltGroupAdrType.name: xylanFltGroupAdrType
xylanFltGroupAdrType.description: This indicates which address is designated first. e.g. If destination is specified, the addresses the OIDs of the rules are ordered <destination> <source>. If the group is an IPX group, this indicator does not affect the OID.

xylanFltRuleListEntry.name: xylanFltRuleListEntry
xylanFltRuleListEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one rule.

xylanFltRuleListIndex.name: xylanFltRuleListIndex
xylanFltRuleListIndex.description: Rule index is made up of the octets of the group name and the network addresses of the rule. It has the following format: IP - <group_name>,0,<adr-4 bytes><mask-4 bytes><adr-4bytes><mask-4 bytes> IPX - <group_name>,0,<net-4 bytes><node-6 bytes>

xylanFltRuleListAdminState.name: xylanFltRuleListAdminState
xylanFltRuleListAdminState.description: The current status of this group. active (1) means the route is functioning, delete (2) tells SNMP to delete the route

xylanFltRuleListRule.name: xylanFltRuleListRule
xylanFltRuleListRule.description: The rule for the address pair. 1) allows traffic for the addresses and 2) rejects all trafic for the pair.

xylanFltServiceTable.name: xylanFltServiceTable
xylanFltServiceTable.description: Service entry for HRE-X filtering feature. This object contains a collection of IP port numbers and filtering Group objects. Thus rules for different service such as FTP or Telnet may be defined.

xylanFltServiceEntry.name: xylanFltServiceEntry
xylanFltServiceEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one service.

xylanFltServiceIndex.name: xylanFltServiceIndex
xylanFltServiceIndex.description: The index is made up of an octet string of ASCII characters containing the name of the service.

xylanFltServiceAdminState.name: xylanFltServiceAdminState
xylanFltServiceAdminState.description: The current status of this group. active (1) means the route is functioning, delete (2) tells SNMP to delete the route

xylanFltServiceNumberTable.name: xylanFltServiceNumberTable
xylanFltServiceNumberTable.description: This table contains the port numbers associated with a particular service.

xylanFltServiceNumberEntry.name: xylanFltServiceNumberEntry
xylanFltServiceNumberEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one port number.

xylanFltServiceNumberIndex.name: xylanFltServiceNumberIndex
xylanFltServiceNumberIndex.description: Service number index is made up of the octets of the group name and the port number: <service_name>,0,<port number-4 bytes>

xylanFltServiceNumberAdminState.name: xylanFltServiceNumberAdminState
xylanFltServiceNumberAdminState.description: The current status of this group. active (1) means the route is functioning, delete (2) tells SNMP to delete the route

xylanFltServiceGroupTable.name: xylanFltServiceGroupTable
xylanFltServiceGroupTable.description: This table contains the groups associated with a particular service.

xylanFltServiceGroupEntry.name: xylanFltServiceGroupEntry
xylanFltServiceGroupEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one group.

xylanFltServiceGroupIndex.name: xylanFltServiceGroupIndex
xylanFltServiceGroupIndex.description: Service group index is made up of the octets of the service name and the group name: <service_name>,0,<group name>

xylanFltServiceGroupAdminState.name: xylanFltServiceGroupAdminState
xylanFltServiceGroupAdminState.description: The current status of this group. active (1) means the route is functioning, delete (2) tells SNMP to delete the route

xylanFltGlobalGroupEntry.name: xylanFltGlobalGroupEntry
xylanFltGlobalGroupEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one group.

xylanFltGlobalGroupIndex.name: xylanFltGlobalGroupIndex
xylanFltGlobalGroupIndex.description: Global group index is made up of the octets of the group name.

xylanFltGlobalGroupAdminState.name: xylanFltGlobalGroupAdminState
xylanFltGlobalGroupAdminState.description: The current status of this group. active (1) means the route is functioning, delete (2) tells SNMP to delete the route

xylanFltGlobalServiceEntry.name: xylanFltGlobalServiceEntry
xylanFltGlobalServiceEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one service.

xylanFltGlobalServiceIndex.name: xylanFltGlobalServiceIndex
xylanFltGlobalServiceIndex.description: Global service index is made up of the octets of the service name.

xylanFltGlobalServiceAdminState.name: xylanFltGlobalServiceAdminState
xylanFltGlobalServiceAdminState.description: The current status of this service. active (1) means the route is functioning, delete (2) tells SNMP to delete the route

xylanFltIpServicePortTbl.name: xylanFltIpServicePortTbl
xylanFltIpServicePortTbl.description: Table that maps a service name to the list of TCP ports it represents.

xylanFltIpServicePortTblEntry.name: xylanFltIpServicePortTblEntry
xylanFltIpServicePortTblEntry.description: Entry in table that maps a service name to the list of TCP ports it represents.

xylanFltIpServicePortName.name: xylanFltIpServicePortName
xylanFltIpServicePortName.description: Name of service for HRE-X Filtering Engine.

xylanFltIpServicePortNumber.name: xylanFltIpServicePortNumber
xylanFltIpServicePortNumber.description: TCP port number assigned to a service for HRE-X Filtering Engine.

xylanFltIpServiceRuleTbl.name: xylanFltIpServiceRuleTbl
xylanFltIpServiceRuleTbl.description: Table that maps a service name to the list of filtering rules. This includes the special service, GLOBAL, which is comprised of the global rules.

xylanFltIpServiceRuleTblEntry.name: xylanFltIpServiceRuleTblEntry
xylanFltIpServiceRuleTblEntry.description: Entry in table that maps a service name (or GLOBAL for global rules to its list of filtering rules.

xylanFltIpServiceRuleName.name: xylanFltIpServiceRuleName
xylanFltIpServiceRuleName.description: Name of service (or Global for global rules) for HRE-X Filtering Engine.

xylanFltIpServiceRuleDest.name: xylanFltIpServiceRuleDest
xylanFltIpServiceRuleDest.description: Destination address for the filtering rule.

xylanFltIpServiceRuleSrc.name: xylanFltIpServiceRuleSrc
xylanFltIpServiceRuleSrc.description: Source address for the filtering rule.

xylanFltIpServiceRuleDisp.name: xylanFltIpServiceRuleDisp
xylanFltIpServiceRuleDisp.description: The disposition for the filtering rule.

xylanFltIpServiceRuleCount.name: xylanFltIpServiceRuleCount
xylanFltIpServiceRuleCount.description: The number of times the filtering rule has been applied.

xylanFltIpServiceRuleGroup.name: xylanFltIpServiceRuleGroup
xylanFltIpServiceRuleGroup.description: Name of group in which the filtering rule is defined.

xylanFltIpxRuleTblEntry.name: xylanFltIpxRuleTblEntry
xylanFltIpxRuleTblEntry.description: Entry in table of IPX filtering rules.

xylanFltIpxRuleType.name: xylanFltIpxRuleType
xylanFltIpxRuleType.description: IPX rules are categorized into four types: Full Address - both the network number and node must match for the rule to be applied Node - only the node must match for the rule to be applied Network - only the network number must match for the rule to be applied Global - this rule type always matches Full Address has the highest precedence, followed by Node, Network, and then Global.

xylanFltIpxRuleDisp.name: xylanFltIpxRuleDisp
xylanFltIpxRuleDisp.description: The disposition for the filtering rule.

xylanFltIpxRuleCount.name: xylanFltIpxRuleCount
xylanFltIpxRuleCount.description: The number of times the filtering rule has been applied.

xylanFltIpxRuleGroup.name: xylanFltIpxRuleGroup
xylanFltIpxRuleGroup.description: Name of group in which the filtering rule is defined.

xylanFltIpQueryDest.name: xylanFltIpQueryDest
xylanFltIpQueryDest.description: Destination IP address to be used in the query.

xylanFltIpQuerySrc.name: xylanFltIpQuerySrc
xylanFltIpQuerySrc.description: Source IP address to be used in the query.

xylanFltIpQueryPort.name: xylanFltIpQueryPort
xylanFltIpQueryPort.description: Destination TCP port to be used in the query. 0 is an indication to not use the port.

xylanFltIpQueryDisp.name: xylanFltIpQueryDisp
xylanFltIpQueryDisp.description: The disposition that results from the query.

xylanFltIpQueryService.name: xylanFltIpQueryService
xylanFltIpQueryService.description: Service that contains the rule that is applied to determine the disposition of the query. The empty string indicates no rule applied.

xylanFltIpQueryRuleID.name: xylanFltIpQueryRuleID
xylanFltIpQueryRuleID.description: Rule ID used to determine the disposition for the query. -1 indicates no rule applied.

xylanFltIpxQueryDisp.name: xylanFltIpxQueryDisp
xylanFltIpxQueryDisp.description: The disposition that results from the query.

xylanFltIpxQueryRuleType.name: xylanFltIpxQueryRuleType
xylanFltIpxQueryRuleType.description: IPX rules are categorized into four types: Full Address - both the network number and node must match for the rule to be applied Node - only the node must match for the rule to be applied Network - only the network number must match for the rule to be applied Global - this rule type always matches Full Address has the highest precedence, followed by Node, Network, and then Global.

xylanFltIpxQueryRuleID.name: xylanFltIpxQueryRuleID
xylanFltIpxQueryRuleID.description: Rule ID used to determine the disposition for the query. -1 is used when no rule applied.

xylanFltActDefaultIpDisp.name: xylanFltActDefaultIpDisp
xylanFltActDefaultIpDisp.description: The current default IP disposition if no other rule applies.

xylanFltActIpPrecedence.name: xylanFltActIpPrecedence
xylanFltActIpPrecedence.description: The current precedence for IP rules.

xylanFltActDefaultIpxDisp.name: xylanFltActDefaultIpxDisp
xylanFltActDefaultIpxDisp.description: The current default IPX disposition if no other rule applies.

xylanFltLastIpDenySrc.name: xylanFltLastIpDenySrc
xylanFltLastIpDenySrc.description: Source IP address for last denied route by HRE-X Filtering.

xylanFltLastIpDenyDest.name: xylanFltLastIpDenyDest
xylanFltLastIpDenyDest.description: Destination IP address for last denied route by HRE-X Filtering.

xylanFltLastIpDenyPort.name: xylanFltLastIpDenyPort
xylanFltLastIpDenyPort.description: Destination IP address for last denied route by HRE-X Filtering.

xylanFltLastIpxDenyNet.name: xylanFltLastIpxDenyNet
xylanFltLastIpxDenyNet.description: Destination IPX network for last denied route by HRE-X Filtering.

xylanFltLastIpxDenyNode.name: xylanFltLastIpxDenyNode
xylanFltLastIpxDenyNode.description: Destination IPX node for last denied route by HRE-X Filtering.

xylanFltLastCommitTrapReason.name: xylanFltLastCommitTrapReason
xylanFltLastCommitTrapReason.description: The reason for the last HRE-X Filtering COMMIT trap; the valid reasons are: 0 - No trap has been sent. 1 - A service that was referenced from the global configuration could not be found. 2 - A group that was referenced from the GLOBAL level or some other service could not be found. 3 - An IPX rule was found in a group assigned to a service rather than the GLOBAL level. 4 - The same port was assigned to two services. 5 - The same service name appears twice. 6 - The same IPX address has two rules associated with it.

xylanFltLastCommitTrapEntity1.name: xylanFltLastCommitTrapEntity1
xylanFltLastCommitTrapEntity1.description: An entity associated with the last HRE-X Filtering COMMIT trap; the value depends on the value of the last xylanFltLastCommitTrapReason. These are: 0 - The data is invalid. 1 - The name of the service that was referenced. 2 - The name of the service that referenced the group. 3 - The name of the service that contained the IPX rule. 4 - The name of the first service to include the port. This service will retain the port. 5 - The service name that appears twice. 6 - The name of the group that contains the second rule for the same IPX address.

xylanFltLastCommitTrapEntity2.name: xylanFltLastCommitTrapEntity2
xylanFltLastCommitTrapEntity2.description: An entity associated with the last HRE-X Filtering COMMIT trap; the value depends on the value of the last xylanFltLastCommitTrapReason. These are: 0 - The data is invalid. 1 - This data item is unused. 2 - The name of the group that could not be found. 3 - The name of the group that contained the IPX rule. 4 - The name of the second service to include the port. This service will not retain the port. 5 - This data item is unused. 6 - The name of the group that contains the first rule for an IPX address for which there is a duplicate.

xylanFltLastCommitTrapPort.name: xylanFltLastCommitTrapPort
xylanFltLastCommitTrapPort.description: The port number associated with the last HRE-X Filtering COMMIT trap; the value depends on the value of the last xylanFltLastCommitTrapReason. These are: 0 - The data is invalid. 1 - This data item is unused. 2 - This data item is unused. 3 - This data item is unused. 4 - The port that was assigned to two services. 5 - This data item is unused. 6 - This data item is unused.

xylanFltLastCommitTrapIpxNet.name: xylanFltLastCommitTrapIpxNet
xylanFltLastCommitTrapIpxNet.description: Destination IPX network for last HRE-X Filtering COMMIT trap; the value depends on the value of the last xylanFltLastCommitTrapReason. These are: 0 - The data is invalid. 1 - This data item is unused. 2 - This data item is unused. 3 - This data item is unused. 4 - This data item is unused. 5 - This data item is unused. 6 - Contains the IPX network number for which there was a duplicate rule.

xylanFltLastCommitTrapIpxNode.name: xylanFltLastCommitTrapIpxNode
xylanFltLastCommitTrapIpxNode.description: Destination IPX node for last HRE-X Filtering COMMIT trap; the value depends on the value of the last xylanFltLastCommitTrapReason. These are: 0 - The data is invalid. 1 - This data item is unused. 2 - This data item is unused. 3 - This data item is unused. 4 - This data item is unused. 5 - This data item is unused. 6 - Contains the IPX node address for which there was a duplicate rule.
